# Argos environment variables (development / contributor template).
#
# Argos runs with zero config locally — SQLite, one-click dev login, all
# defaults. Every entry here is optional and commented out; uncomment only what
# you want to override. The full menu of advanced settings (worker limits,
# queue sizes, live-demo tuning, …) lives in docs/CONFIGURATION.md.
#
# OAuth apps and the Claude token are managed in the UI (Configuration → OAuth
# Apps and the onboarding wizard), not via ENV.
#
# Self-host operators don't use this file — install.sh ships
# .tools/docker/.env.example with the OPS-level keys (ports, image tag, secrets)
# and writes a populated .env into the install directory.

# ── Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# APP_ENV=local                       # local | staging | production
# APP_DEBUG=true
# APP_KEY=                            # auto-generated on first manager boot
# APP_URL=http://localhost             # source of truth: host, scheme, session
#                                      # cookie domain and live-demo subdomains
#                                      # all derive from this. Must be publicly
#                                      # reachable for webhook mode.

# ── Database (defaults to SQLite; the compose stack sets mariadb) ─────────────
# DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
# DB_DATABASE=/path/to/argos.sqlite

# ── Media Library ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MEDIA_DISK=public                   # filesystem disk for uploaded media files

# ── DemoSeeder (.tools/bin/dev-reset.sh) — optional, dev only ────────────────
# Only read while seeding; a missing value is skipped. Credentials are normally
# created via the onboarding UI — these just pre-seed a dev environment.
# SEED_USER_EMAIL=admin@argos.local
# SEED_REPO_URL=https://github.com/nodus-it/argos.git
# SEED_CLAUDE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# Codex auth: base64 -w0 ~/.codex/auth.json
# SEED_CODEX_AUTH_JSON_B64=
